Monday8pm(x) ::: x is on some Mondays at 8 pm.

RealityTV(x) ::: x is a reality TV show.
BreakingBad(x) ::: x is Breaking Bad.

∃x (Monday8pm(x) ∧ RoseTV(x)) ::: On some Mondays at 8 pm, roses are given out on TV.
∀x (RoseTV(x) → Bachelor(x)) ::: Every rose given out on TV is on the Bachelor.
∀x (Bachelor(x) → RealPeople(x)) ::: Everything on the Bachelor portrays the lives of real people.
∀x (RealPeople(x) → RealityTV(x)) ::: All shows portraying the lives of real people are reality TV shows.
¬RealityTV(breakingBad) ::: Breaking Bad is not a reality TV show.
Conclusion:
∀x (RoseTV(x) ∧ BreakingBad(x)) → Monday8pm(x) ::: If roses are given out during Breaking Bad, then it is on Monday at 8 pm.

Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? If roses are given out during Breaking Bad, then it is on Monday at 8 pm.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Monday8pm(x) ::: x is on some Mondays at 8 pm.
RoseTV(x) ::: x is a rose given out on TV.
Bachelor(x) ::: x is on the Bachelor.
RealPeople(x) ::: x portrays the lives of real people.
RealityTV(x) ::: x is a reality TV show.
BreakingBad(x) ::: x is Breaking Bad.
Premises:
∃x (Monday8pm(x) ∧ RoseTV(x)) ::: On some Mondays at 8 pm, roses are given out on TV.
∀x (RoseTV(x) → Bachelor(x)) ::: Every rose given out on TV is on the Bachelor.
∀x (Bachelor(x) → RealPeople(x)) ::: Everything on the Bachelor portrays the lives of real people.
∀x (RealPeople(x) → RealityTV(x)) ::: All shows portraying the lives of real people are reality TV shows.
¬RealityTV(breakingBad) ::: Breaking Bad is not a reality TV show.
Conclusion:
∀x (RoseTV(x) ∧ BreakingBad(x)) → Monday8pm(x) ::: If roses are given out during Breaking Bad, then it is on Monday at 8 pm.
